# Autotest on Python 3.11

## Tech stack:

- [python 3.11](https://www.python.org)
- [playwright](https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-python)
- [pyperclip](https://github.com/asweigart/pyperclip)

## Description:

This autotest is used to check the user's authorization on the site:

1. To get started, you are logged into the site
 
2. Automatic data entry: 'Login' and 'Password'
   
3. Copy APIkey

4. Send request on selected endpoint

5. Check's getting response

## How to use:

Install Python 3.11

Install Playwright for Python:

`pip3 install playwright`

Install the required browsers:

`playwright install`

Install Pyperclip for Python

`pip3 install pyperclip`

Run file 'autorization.py':

 `python3 autorization.py`